parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the brakes to stick or lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on other brake components.
symptoms: Rear brake caliper freezes or sticks
rear brake rotor rusts or corrodes
metal-to-metal sound when applying brakes
brake pedal goes to the floor
extended stopping distance
and intermittent brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on other brake components.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
extended stopping distance
intermittent brake failure
and brake fluid leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake components can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on other brake components.
symptoms: Corrosion of rear brake calipers
corrosion of rear brake rotors
and rusting of brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake pads can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on other brake components.
symptoms: Excessive wear of brake pads
frequent replacement of brake pads
and uneven wear of brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cradle bolts can cause the engine to fall out of the vehicle, leading to a loss of steering capability and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The engine falls out of the vehicle
the vehicle has no steering capability
the rear frame/cradle bolts and retainer separate
the vehicle makes a loud noise
and the consumer feels a thump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete repair of the recall can lead to the failure of the rear cradle bolts, causing the engine to fall out of the vehicle and resulting in a loss of steering capability.
symptoms: The dealer only replaces the front cradle bolts and retainers
ignoring the rear cradle bolts
which can lead to the engine falling out of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Cradle Bolts and Retainers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the cradle bolts and retainers can cause the engine to fall out of the vehicle, leading to a loss of steering capability and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The cradle bolts and retainers are severely corroded
the bolts are not "lock-tight
" and the bushings are corroded
making it impossible to perform alignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the digital dashboard can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and other critical information, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The digital dashboard displays erratic behavior
flashing on and off
or not displaying correct speed or mileage; the dashboard goes black
making it impossible to determine the vehicle's speed; the dashboard fails to display fuel level
odometer
or other critical information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving; the battery is drained or replaced frequently; the alternator is replaced multiple times; the vehicle's electrical system is prone to short circuits or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring defects can cause electrical system failures, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The wiring system is prone to short circuits or fires; the dashboard components do not work properly; the vehicle's electrical system is prone to malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
